{{Infobox sport tournament | name = 1952 Basque Pelota World Championships | image = 1952 Basque Pelota World Championships poster.png | caption = Tournament poster | location = {{flagicon|Spain}} [[San Sebastián]], [[Spain]] | start_date = 28 August | end_date = September | administrator = [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]] | tournament_format = | venues = | teams = 8 | purse = | champions = {{flag|France}} | runners-up1 = {{flag|Spain}} | runners-up2 = {{flag|Argentina}} | matches = | points = | attendance = | previous = | next = [[1955 Basque Pelota World Championships|1955]] | website = }}
The '''1952 Basque Pelota World Championships''' were the 1st edition of the [[Basque Pelota World Championships]] organized by the [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]].
==Participating nations== {{col-begin|width=70%}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Argentina}} *{{flag|Cuba}} *{{flag|France}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Italy}} *{{flag|Mexico}} *{{flag|Philippines}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Spain}} *{{flag|Uruguay}} {{col-end}}
