{{Infobox football match | title = 1983 Israel Super Cup | image = | event = | team1 = [[Maccabi Netanya F.C.|Maccabi Netaya]] | team1association = | team1score = 1 | team2 = [[Hapoel Tel Aviv F.C.|Hapoel Tel Aviv]] | team2association = | team2score = 0 | details = | date = 14 June 1983 | stadium = [[Ramat Gan Stadium]] | city = [[Ramat Gan]] | man_of_the_match1a = | man_of_the_match1atitle = | man_of_the_match1b = | man_of_the_match1btitle = | referee = [[Arie Prost]] | attendance = 1,500 | weather = | previous = [[1982 Israel Super Cup|1982]] | next = [[1984 Israel Super Cup|1984]] }}
The '''1983 Israel Super Cup''' was the 13th [[Israel Super Cup]] (18th, including unofficial matches, as the competition wasn't played within the [[Israel Football Association]] in its first 5 editions, until 1969), an annual Israel football match played between the winners of the previous season's [[Liga Leumit|Top Division]] and [[Israel State Cup]].
The match was played between [[Maccabi Netanya F.C.|Maccabi Netanya]], champions of the [[1982–83 Liga Leumit]] and [[Hapoel Tel Aviv F.C.|Hapoel Tel Aviv]], winners of the [[1982–83 Israel State Cup]].
This was Maccabi Netanya's 5th Israel Super Cup appearance and Hapoel Tel Aviv's 6th (including unofficial matches). At the match, played at [[Ramat Gan Stadium]], Maccabi Netanya won 1–0.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/israsupcuphist.html Israel - List of 'Champions of Champions' (Super Cup) Finals] Yaniv Bleicher, 3 July 2008, RSSSF</ref><ref>[http://jhpress.nli.org.il/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Source=Page&Skin=TAUHe&BaseHref=DAV/1983/06/15&PageLabelPrint=4&EntityId=Ar00410&ViewMode=HTML Benny Lam Awarded Netanya the Champion of Champions Cup]{{Dead link|date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Moshe Cohen, Davar, 15 June 1983, Historical Jewish Press {{he icon}}</ref>
