{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox golf facility | name = Jorhat Gymkhana Club | image = Jorhat Gymkhana Club.jpg | imagesize = 250px | caption = Jorhat Gymkhana Club | pushpin_map = | location = Club Road, [[Jorhat]], [[Assam]] 785008 | coordinates = {{coord|26.732608|94.222263|region:IN|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | establishment = {{start date and age|1876}} | type = | owner = | operator = | holes = 9 | tournaments = | website = }}
'''Jorhat Gymkhana Club''' is a sports venue located in [[Jorhat]], [[Assam]]. Club built in 1876 by D. Slimmons. The club has been a venue for horse races, lawn tennis grass courts, swimming pool, billiards, polo, golf, cricket etc. ever since its inauguration. The Governor's Cup is played here every year with a lush green 9-hole golf course circuit.<ref>[http://jorhat.gov.in/jorhat-gymkhana-club-in-jorhat.html Jorhat District]</ref>
The club's golf course is list into the World Heritage list as the oldest golf course in Asia and the third oldest in the world.<ref>[http://jorhatgymkhanagolf.golfgaga.com/ Jorhat Gymkhana Club Golf]</ref> The club offers facilities in lawn tennis grass courts, swimming pool, billiards, polo, gentleman's bar and cinema theatre. The cricket ground here is known as Jorhat Gymkhana Ground and has a capacity of 8,000 as well as has a turf wicket. The ground hosted the [[CK Naidu Trophy]] which is Under-19 Indian Cricket tournament matches.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://content-www.cricinfo.com/india/content/ground/58192.html |title = Jorhat Gymkhana Ground |publisher = [[Cricinfo.com]] |accessdate = 2008-11-13}}</ref> The club is home of Khelmati sports club uses this ground for practising cricket and The Club road was the first asphalt road laid which connect the City Centre with the Jorhat Gymkhana Club.<ref>[http://www.bharatonline.com/assam/jorhat/jorhat-gymkhana.html Bharatonline]</ref>
