{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Merefield Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Rochdale]], [[Lancashire]] | establishment = 1855 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1860 | club1 = [[North of England cricket team|North]] | date = 4 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/711.html profile }}
'''Merefield Ground''' was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Rochdale]], [[Lancashire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1855, when the Heally Club played a United England Eleven.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/711_misc.html Other matches played on Merefield Ground]</ref>
In 1860, the ground held its only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match when the [[North of England cricket team|North]] played the [[South of England cricket team|South]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/711_f.html First-Class Matches played on Merefield Ground]</ref>
The final recorded match on the ground came in 1888 when [[Rochdale Cricket Club|Rochdale]] played the [[Parsees cricket team|Parsees]] during [[Parsee cricket team in England in 1888|their tour of England]]. The ground was later required for building and built over. The exact location of the ground is unknown.
